---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import EmailSignup from '../../components/EmailSignup.astro';
import BookSchema from '../../components/BookSchema.astro';

const amazonUrl = 'https://www.amazon.com/Thread-Gold-Pairing-Caleb-Arlow/dp/B0GNKB2N8Q/';
const sampleUrl = 'https://www.amazon.com/Thread-Gold-Pairing-Caleb-Arlow/dp/B0GNKB2N8Q/#reader_B0GNKB2N8Q';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Thread of Gold · Book One of The Pairing"
  description="Lira's thread is gold. Gold isn't supposed to exist. Book One of The Pairing by Caleb Arlow. Free with Kindle Unlimited."
  ogImage="/covers/thread-of-gold.png"
>
  <BookSchema
    name="Thread of Gold"
    bookNumber={1}
    cover="/covers/thread-of-gold.png"
    url="/books/thread-of-gold"
    amazonUrl={amazonUrl}
    description="Lira's thread is gold. Gold isn't supposed to exist. Tieran is on the other end of it, and the system that paired them has never seen a bond like this. Book One of The Pairing, a 12-book YA fantasy romance series."
  />
  <section class="section" style="padding-top: var(--s-9);">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p style="margin-bottom: var(--s-5);">
        <a class="btn-text" href="/books" style="color: var(--paper-300);">← All books</a>
      </p>

      <div class="book-detail">
        <div class="book-cover">
          <img src="/covers/thread-of-gold.png" alt="Thread of Gold cover" />
        </div>

        <div>
          <p class="t-eyebrow">Book One · Discovery arc · Free in KU</p>
          <h1 class="book-detail-title">
            Thread of <span class="em-italic">Gold.</span>
          </h1>
          <div class="book-detail-meta">
            <span>YA Fantasy Romance</span><span class="dot">·</span>
            <span>~104K words</span><span class="dot">·</span>
            <span>33 chapters</span><span class="dot">·</span>
            <span>Ages 14+</span>
          </div>

          <div class="trope-row">
            <span class="trope">Fated bond</span>
            <span class="trope">Slow burn</span>
            <span class="trope">Forbidden romance</span>
            <span class="trope">Color magic</span>
            <span class="trope">Dystopian</span>
          </div>

          <p class="body-text">
            Lira's thread is gold. Gold isn't supposed to exist.
          </p>
          <p class="body-text">
            She's thirteen the day she gets paired. Tieran is on the other end of her thread, and the second they touch the bond lights up in a color the Threadweavers have spent forty years pretending isn't real. They say their job is to protect pairings. What they actually do is read them, sort them, and end the ones they don't like.
          </p>
          <p class="body-text">
            Gold means love that isn't supposed to happen inside a system built to engineer it. Lira and Tieran were not supposed to happen.
          </p>

          <p class="book-detail-pull">
            "She is thirteen years old and she is already the variable they cannot solve for."
          </p>

          <p class="body-text">
            Thread of Gold opens the Discovery arc of The Pairing, a 12-book YA fantasy romance series. For readers of <em>Matched</em>, <em>Delirium</em>, <em>Red Queen</em>, and <em>Powerless</em>.
          </p>

          <div class="book-detail-actions">
            <a class="btn btn-primary" href={amazonUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read on Amazon · Free in KU</a>
            <a class="btn btn-ghost" href={sampleUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read a sample</a>
          </div>
          <p style="margin-top: var(--s-3); font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--fg-muted);">
            Or <a href="/books/thread-of-silver" style="color: var(--thread-gold);">continue to Book Two →</a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-tinted">
    <div class="wrap">
      <EmailSignup
        headline="Get Book Four first."
        sub="New release alerts, cover reveals, and early chapters land in the newsletter before they go anywhere else."
      />
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .trope-row {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--s-2);
    margin: 0 0 var(--s-5);
  }
  .trope {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--paper-100);
    background: rgba(201, 168, 97, 0.10);
    border: 1px solid rgba(201, 168, 97, 0.30);
    padding: 0.4rem 0.7rem;
  }
</style>
